Privacy Policy
Shenzhen Proudlong  Health  Co., Ltd. ("we" or "us") develops and manages the BodyWave app ("the App"), a freemium service designed to provide features at no cost and may offer premium features through in-app purchases. This Privacy Policy aims to transparently outline how we collect, use, process, and share your personal information and how you can control your privacy settings.
Information Collection and Use
To enhance the user experience in our App, we may ask you to provide certain personally identifiable information. The types of information we may collect include:
Usage information
Health data (collected via Apple Health APIs only with your explicit consent)
We commit to using the collected personal information solely for providing and improving the service and not sharing it with any third party except as described in this Privacy Policy.
Third-Party Services
The App may utilize third-party services to help improve service quality. These third-party services include, but are not limited to, Google Analytics for Firebase. We recommend reviewing the privacy policies of these third-party service providers to understand how they handle your information.
Special Note on Health Data
We place great importance on the privacy and security of your health data. With your explicit consent, we may access specific health data through Apple's APIs. We will never use your health data for marketing, advertising, or use-based data mining purposes. All health data processed through Apple Health will remain on your device and not be uploaded or stored on any servers.
Data Security
We commit to protecting your personal information using commercially acceptable means to prevent unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, please note that no security measures are infallible.
Children's Privacy
The App is not targeted at children under the age of 10. If we discover that personal information from children under 10 has been collected, we will take steps to delete the information immediately. If you believe we might have accidentally collected such information, please contact us promptly.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to update or change our Privacy Policy at any time. Such changes will be posted on this page, and the update's effective date will be revised. We encourage users to review this Privacy Policy regularly to stay informed about how we protect your information.
Contact Us
If you have any questions or suggestions about our Privacy Policy, please do not hesitate to contact us at
BodyWaveFeedback@protonmail.com
